      "writtenOn": "2018-05-22T17:14:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We usually use \"local matrix\" for cases where a SkShader or some other effect transforms local coords (e.g. there is a SkLocalMatrixShader which transforms local coords by a matrix and then invokes an inner SkShader with those coords).\n\nIn other places we\u0027ve called this \"fViewMatrixIfUsingLocalCoords\" which is somewhat verbose.",
